# BCD (Business Control Dashboard) â€” Multi-Account Migration Strategy

> **Parent Page:** Contact Centre â€“ AWS Multi-Account Architecture Review  
> **Status:** Draft  
> **Author:** Virender Singh  
> **Date:** February 2026  
> **Reference Model:** Personalization in IVR â€“ Multi-Account Architecture

---

## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Purpose

This document presents the strategy for migrating the **Business Control Dashboard (BCD)** from the shared Universal BCD Stack in the current TC-15 account into its own dedicated AWS account. It follows the same migration pattern established by the Personalization in IVR workload, which demonstrated a successful, low-risk approach to isolating loosely coupled platform services into separate AWS accounts.

### 1.2 Background

The BCD is a critical internal tool used by business operations teams to manage queue configurations, routing decisions, and real-time operational controls for the contact centre. Today, all BCD components â€” including the Micro Front End, Queue Control service, Decision Engine, and associated DynamoDB tables â€” run within the **Universal BCD Stack** inside the shared **TC-15** AWS account.

While this shared model simplified initial deployment, it introduces several challenges as the platform scales:

- **Blast radius risk**: A misconfiguration or failed deployment in BCD can impact other services in TC-15 (IVR, Chat, etc.)
- **IAM over-permissioning**: BCD resources share IAM boundaries with unrelated workloads
- **Cost obscurity**: BCD operational costs are commingled with other TC-15 workloads
- **Deployment coupling**: BCD release cycles are constrained by shared CI/CD pipelines and Lambda concurrency limits

### 1.3 Scope

This strategy covers:

- Current state architecture of BCD within TC-15
- Proposed target design with BCD in a dedicated AWS account
- Comprehensive considerations and benefits analysis
- Migration approach and phasing
- Alignment with the broader multi-account strategy

---

## 2. Current State Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

The BCD currently operates as part of the **Universal BCD Stack** within the **TC-15 AWS account**. The architecture consists of the following key components:

