### 2.2 Component Inventory

| Component | Service Type | Description |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| **Micro Front End** | S3 + CloudFront | React-based dashboard UI for business users |
| **Queue Control** | Lambda | Manages queue configurations and routing rules |
| **Decision Engine** | Lambda | Executes business routing logic and decision trees |
| **CX Session Store** | DynamoDB | Stores session data and operational state |
| **Transfer to Queue** | SQS/Lambda | Manages queue transfer operations |
| **API Gateway** | API Gateway | Exposes BCD APIs for front-end consumption |

### 2.3 Integration Points

The BCD has the following integration points with other TC-15 services:

1. **AWS Connect** â€” The Decision Engine feeds routing decisions back to Connect contact flows
2. **SNS Topics** â€” BCD subscribes to event notifications for real-time updates
3. **IVR Core Lambdas** â€” Some shared Lambda layers and environment configurations
4. **CloudWatch** â€” Shared monitoring and logging within TC-15 account
5. **IAM Roles** â€” Shared IAM boundary with all TC-15 workloads

### 2.4 Current Challenges

| Challenge | Impact | Severity |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| Shared blast radius with IVR core | A BCD deployment failure can affect live customer calls | ğŸ”´ High |
| Commingled IAM permissions | BCD Lambdas have broader permissions than necessary | ğŸŸ  Medium |
| No independent cost tracking | Cannot determine true BCD operational cost | ğŸŸ  Medium |
| Shared Lambda concurrency | BCD and IVR compete for Lambda concurrent executions | ğŸ”´ High |
| Coupled deployment pipeline | BCD releases are constrained by TC-15 change windows | ğŸŸ¡ Low |
| Shared DynamoDB capacity | CX Session Store competes with other DynamoDB tables | ğŸŸ  Medium |

